## Road boards.

##### 43 Section [14][105], [Reserves and other Lands Disposal and Public Bodies Empowering Act 1914][106], repealed
    
*   Whereas by section [fourteen][105] of the [Reserves and other Lands Disposal and Public Bodies Empowering Act 1914][106], certain powers of Borough Councils with respect to drainage and sanitation were conferred on the One Tree Hill, the Epsom, and the Eden Terrace Road Boards: And whereas the Epsom and the Eden Terrace Road Boards have been dissolved: And whereas by an Order in Council under the Counties Act 1920, dated the third day of October, nineteen hundred and twenty-seven, and published in the _Gazette_ of the sixth day of the same month, certain powers of Borough Councils with respect to drainage and sanitation (including the powers defined in the said section [fourteen][105]) were conferred on the One Tree Hill Road Board: Be it therefore enacted as follows:---
    
    Section [fourteen][105] of the [Reserves and other Lands Disposal and Public Bodies Empowering Act 1914][106], is hereby repealed.

##### 44 Special provision with respect to certain drainage and sewerage loans raised by One Tree Hill Road Board
    
*   Whereas on the twenty-ninth day of August, nineteen hundred and twenty-three, the One Tree Hill Road Board (hereinafter called the Board) was authorized by a vote of ratepayers in accordance with the provisions of the Local Bodies' Loans Act 1913, to raise a special loan of thirty-six dollars (hereinafter referred to as No 1 loan) for (a) the construction of drainage reticulation in that part of the Board's district known as the Western Area, and (b) the construction of an outfall sewer from the Royal Oak to the sea at the Manukau Harbour, together with a settling-tank in connection with such sewer: And whereas on the seventh day of November, nineteen hundred and twenty-three, the Board was authorized in manner aforesaid to raise a special loan of thirty-six dollars (hereinafter referred to as No 2 loan) for the construction of drainage reticulation in that portion of the Board's district known as the Eastern Area: And whereas owing to an alteration in the drainage scheme the outfall sewer and settling-tank authorized to be constructed out of No 1 loan were not constructed, and the sum of eight thousand seven hundred dollars out of such loan was used in constructing a pumping-station and rising-main: And whereas after the completion of the drainage reticulation for which No 1 loan was raised and the construction of the said pumping-station and rising-main the Board has a surplus unexpended of the proceeds of No 1 loan amounting to three thousand four hundred dollars: And whereas the proceeds of No 2 loan were insufficient to complete the drainage reticulation for which such loan was raised, and the Board resolved to borrow a further sum not exceeding ten per centum of the amount of the No 2 loan in pursuance of the power conferred on it by section nineteen of the Local Bodies' Loans Act 1926: And whereas by agreement bearing date the twentieth day of January, nineteen hundred and twenty-six, made between the Board of the one part and the Auckland and Suburban Drainage Board of the other part it was agreed that the said Western and Eastern Areas should be included within the Auckland and Suburban Drainage District, and in pursuance of the terms of the said agreement there is now due and payable from and by the Board to the Drainage Board the sum of two thousand and thirty-one dollars and sixty cents in respect of the Western Area, and the sum of one thousand five hundred and ninety-two dollars, sixty and two thirds cents in respect of the Eastern Area: And whereas it is desired that the Board's action in expending the said sum of eight thousand seven hundred dollars out of the proceeds of No 1 loan for the construction of a pumping-station and rising-main should be validated, and further that the Board should be authorized to pay to the Auckland and Suburban Drainage Board the sum of two thousand and thirty-one dollars and sixty cents out of the surplus proceeds of No 1 loan, and the sum of one thousand five hundred and ninety-two dollars, sixty and two thirds cents from the sum of two thousand four hundred dollars to be raised by the Board as aforesaid: Be it therefore enacted as follows:---
    
    (1) The expenditure by the Board out of the proceeds of No 1 loan of the sum of eight thousand seven hundred dollars in the construction of a pumping-station and rising-main is hereby validated.
    
    (2) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in the Local Bodies' Loans Act 1926, or any other Act, the Board is hereby authorized to pay to the Auckland and Suburban Drainage Board the sum of two thousand and thirty-one dollars and sixty cents out of the unexpended surplus of the proceeds of No 1 loan, and the sum of one thousand five hundred and ninety-two dollars, sixty and two thirds cents out of the sum of two thousand four hundred dollars about to be raised by the Board for the completion of the drainage of the Eastern Area.
    
    The expressions ""thirty-six dollars"", ""eight thousand seven hundred dollars"", ""three thousand four hundred dollars"", ""two thousand and thirty-one dollars and sixty cents"", ""one thousand five hundred and ninety-two dollars, sixty and two thirds cents"", and ""two thousand four hundred dollars"" were substituted, as from 10 July 1967, for the expressions ""eighteen thousand pounds"", ""four thousand three hundred and fifty pounds"", ""one thousand seven hundred pounds"", ""one thousand and fifteen pounds sixteen shillings"", ""seven hundred and ninety-six pounds six shillings and twopence"", and ""one thousand two hundred pounds"" respectively, pursuant to section [7(1)][97] Decimal Currency Act 1964 (1964 No 27).

